26
00:01:55,510 --> 00:01:57,870
Yeah? And yet you carry 2 of them.

27
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:17,310
When I joined the bau,gideon said to me,

28
00:02:17,350 --> 00:02:19,660
"you don't have to carry a gun to kill someone."

29
00:02:19,700 --> 00:02:21,470
- I don't get it.
- You will.

30
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:23,260
Good luck tomorrow.

31
00:02:51,330 --> 00:02:54,400
- Reid failed his qualification.
- He can re-test in 2 weeks.

32
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:58,110
Yeah,but he's gonna be embarrassed about it,so let's not mention it.

33
00:02:58,130 --> 00:03:00,880
Yeah,let's not.

34
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,840
Not a word.

35
00:03:10,790 --> 00:03:12,020
Hey.

36
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:15,060
We're all here for you.

37
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,430
I'm serious.

38
00:03:17,890 --> 00:03:20,250
If you ever need anything...

39
00:03:23,260 --> 00:03:25,530
Just blow on that.

40
00:03:27,250 --> 00:03:30,150
Ok,franklin park,des plaines,yesterday afternoon.

41
00:03:30,190 --> 00:03:31,590
3 victims shot at distance.

42
00:03:31,610 --> 00:03:34,320
It's the third such shooting in 2 weeks.

43
00:03:34,820 --> 00:03:37,400
- A sniper?
- We don't use that word.

44
00:03:37,430 --> 00:03:38,160
Why not?

45
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:42,420
The public perception is that the fbi doesn't have an exemplary record with snipers.

46
00:03:42,420 --> 00:03:46,020
Besides,a sniper is a professional marksman.These guys aren't snipers.

47
00:03:46,060 --> 00:03:48,440
- What do we call 'em then?
- L.D.S.K.

48
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:51,460
Long distance serial killers.

49
00:03:51,490 --> 00:03:54,080
How many of these guys have we caught using a profile?

50
00:03:54,110 --> 00:03:55,780
None.

51
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:02,470
Criminal Minds

52
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:10,700
-=www.ydy.com/bbs=-
Proudly Presents

53
00:04:24,580 --> 00:04:32,800
Sync:YTET-fisherchen
-=www.ydy.com/bbs=-

54
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:36,130
2 weeks,3 shooting incidents,6 victims,all shot in the abdomen.

55
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:39,030
First and only fatality,henry sachs,married,father of 3,

56
00:04:39,060 --> 00:04:41,410
was shot in a shopping center parking lot.

57
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:42,260
9 days later,

58
00:04:42,290 --> 00:04:47,120
doug miller and kevin parks were playing basketball at a community center.

59
00:04:47,170 --> 00:04:51,390
Franklin park,4 days later,jerry middleton,kate murray,and tim reilly.

60
00:04:51,420 --> 00:04:54,430
Des plaines police have found no link between any of the victims.

61
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:55,230
Ballistics?

62
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:57,550
He's using frangible rounds,which fragment on impact,

63
00:04:57,580 --> 00:04:59,380
making ballistics comparisons impossible.

64
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:01,800
The good news is that all the park victims are gonna make it.

65
00:05:01,830 --> 00:05:04,170
The bad new is that none of them saw anything.

66
00:05:04,210 --> 00:05:07,540
However,one of the patients does have an intact bullet lodged in his spine.

67
00:05:07,580 --> 00:05:08,760
What's the prognosis?

68
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,530
There's a disagreement among surgical staff

69
00:05:10,570 --> 00:05:13,980
as to whether they can remove the slug without paralyzing the patient.

70
00:05:14,030 --> 00:05:17,940
Well,without a useful witness or a solid piece of forensic evidence...

71
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:20,910
the profile's all we'll have.

72
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:27,080
Nietzsche wrote,

73
00:05:27,110 --> 00:05:28,920
"the irrationality of a thing

74
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:31,550
"is not an argument against it's existence,

75
00:05:31,580 --> 00:05:34,630
rather,a condition of it."

76
00:05:34,730 --> 00:05:35,910
L.D.S.K.S are so rare,

77
00:05:35,950 --> 00:05:37,720
we haven't been able to build a standard profile.

78
00:05:37,740 --> 00:05:39,510
Here's what we do know:They're always male,

79
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:42,400
and they frequently have law enforcement or military experience,

80
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:44,470
and they always contact the police or the media.

81
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:46,980
To take credit or relive the experience?

82
00:05:47,010 --> 00:05:48,190
Both.

83
00:05:48,230 --> 00:05:52,230
All serial killers attempt to relive the ecstasy they get from their killings.

84
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:54,300
Some use souvenirs taken from the victims,

85
00:05:54,350 --> 00:06:00,270
and others return to the dump site to interact with the body.

86
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:02,210
Both modes require contact with the victim,

87
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:05,840
contact which,by definition,long distance serial killers don't have.

88
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:08,490
The beltway shooters left a tarot card at one of their crime scenes.

89
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:11,310
Later they called a tip hotline,which ultimately led to their capture.

90
00:06:11,350 --> 00:06:13,600
But our unsub hasn't contacted anybody.

91
00:06:13,650 --> 00:06:15,230
He will.

92
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:17,200
Until he does,what do we have?

93
00:06:17,230 --> 00:06:19,710
Sometimes it's not what the unsub does that reveals the profile.

94
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:22,470
Sometimes it is what they do not do.

95
00:06:22,510 --> 00:06:24,400
He doesn't kill his victims.

96
00:06:24,430 --> 00:06:26,150
Underkill's a unique signature.

97
00:06:26,180 --> 00:06:26,730
The question is,

98
00:06:26,780 --> 00:06:29,480
does he shoot them in the stomach intentionally just to wound them,

99
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:33,080
or is he just aiming at the biggest part of the target?

100
00:06:34,070 --> 00:06:37,900
Specifically,does the unsub lack the skill to make the head shot,

101
00:06:37,940 --> 00:06:40,780
or simply the will to take it?

102
00:06:52,490 --> 00:06:53,670
Agent hotchner.

103
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:57,040
Detective calvin,this is agent morgan,agent reid.

104
00:06:57,080 --> 00:06:59,340
Thanks for comin'.Follow me.

105
00:07:00,070 --> 00:07:03,640
The cones mark the places where the victims were,

106
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:07,090
so we know he fired from somewhere in this area.

107
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,710
Close enough to hit all 3 victims,

108
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:13,820
but far away enough not to be seen.

109
00:07:14,020 --> 00:07:18,890
His wounding his victims intentionally would classify him as a sadistic killer.

110
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:20,920
That would help us?

111
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:23,030
We know a lot about sadists.

112
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:25,380
But most want to be close to their victims to watch them suffer.

113
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:28,390
A powerful scope would allow him to observe it from a safe distance

114
00:07:28,430 --> 00:07:30,930
So how do we determine if he's a sadist?

115
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,940
We spend some time in his shoes.

116
00:07:32,970 --> 00:07:34,880
We let him tell us.

117
00:07:40,970 --> 00:07:42,800
Come on,barry,you don't know that!

118
00:07:42,850 --> 00:07:44,400
Good morning,doctors.

119
00:07:44,450 --> 00:07:47,350
Forgive us.We were just reviewing the cases at hand.

120
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:50,110
This is dr. Neil erstadt,chief of surgery,

121
00:07:50,150 --> 00:07:52,980
and our trauma specialist,dr. Barry landman.

122
00:07:53,020 --> 00:07:57,370
These are the fbi profilers,agents gideon,jareau,greenaway.

123
00:07:57,410 --> 00:07:59,200
How are you?

124
00:07:59,260 --> 00:08:00,910
Forgive me.I don't shake.

125
00:08:00,930 --> 00:08:02,970
My hands,you understand?

126
00:08:03,450 --> 00:08:04,660
Of course.

127
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:07,610
So as psychological profilers,s,what exactly are you looking for?

128
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:09,730
How the victims were shot.

129
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:11,950
That could reveal the shooter's signature behavior.

130
00:08:11,980 --> 00:08:15,570
These separate wound channels blossom from the entrance wounds.

131
00:08:15,610 --> 00:08:17,510
You can see the trauma's extensive.

132
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:19,970
- You performed the surgeries?
- On patient miller.

133
00:08:20,020 --> 00:08:22,490
I consulted with dr. Landman on the others.

134
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:26,130
The intact slug lodged between the l4-l5 vertebrae.

135
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:28,600
Any attempt to remove it,would likely leave the patient paralyzed.

136
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:30,440
In your opinion.

137
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:32,390
In my opinion.

138
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,320
Disagree?

139
00:08:33,340 --> 00:08:36,100
- With the right surgeon,there is no risk.
- There's always risk.

140
00:08:36,130 --> 00:08:39,320
What significance does the bullet have in building a profile?

141
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:43,770
Well,even if we can't get a ballistics match,we can get a rifle type,

142
00:08:43,830 --> 00:08:45,680
and the specific type of rifle the suspect uses,

143
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:47,710
that could be very significant to the profile.

144
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:50,550
You believe you can safely perform the surgery,dr. Landman?

145
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:52,630
I know I can.

146
00:08:57,630 --> 00:09:02,140
This handicapped spot couldn't be further away from the entrance to the building.

147
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:03,410
Yeah?

148
00:09:03,470 --> 00:09:07,420
It also has line of sight to all 3 victims and the flagpole.

149
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,770
What are you thinkin'?

150
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:14,520
At this range,the unsub would have to factor in wind direction and speed as he shot.

151
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:22,970
To do this,he needed a spot with the widest field of fire and line of sight to the flagpole.

152
00:09:23,010 --> 00:09:24,720
He came here before the shooting,

153
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:27,760
decided this was his spot...

154
00:09:28,350 --> 00:09:32,300
and ensured that it would be empty when he came back.

155
00:09:35,540 --> 00:09:37,920
My guess is he's shooting from his car.

156
00:09:37,950 --> 00:09:40,310
Well,that would mean he wanted to get away from here quickly,

157
00:09:40,340 --> 00:09:42,550
that he didn't stick around to watch his victims suffer.

158
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:44,770
So he would not be a sadist.

159
00:09:44,810 --> 00:09:45,880
What would he be?

160
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:50,900
A very smart,very resourceful,very paranoid sociopath.

161
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:56,700
If I'm the unsub,why do I shoot my victims between 2:55 and 3:15?

162
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:59,010
That's when I'd do it.There are fewer cops on the street.

163
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:01,590
- Why is that?
- Well,the police overlap shifts

164
00:10:01,630 --> 00:10:04,030
so there's always someone minding the store.

165
00:10:04,070 --> 00:10:06,790
Second shift starts at 3:00,first shift walks at 3:30.

166
00:10:06,810 --> 00:10:09,260
Wouldn't there be twice as many cops on the street at that time?

167
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:10,650
In theory.

168
00:10:10,710 --> 00:10:12,270
The first half-hour of your shift,you're in roll call.

169
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:13,760
You're not on the street.

170
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:15,440
And the last half-hour,you're at the station.

171
00:10:15,480 --> 00:10:17,210
You're finishin' reports,you're booking prisoners,

172
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:19,680
so the 25 minutes around the first/second shift,

173
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:21,480
that's a bad guy's golden window.

174
00:10:21,510 --> 00:10:25,320
How many people outside law enforcement would know that?

175
00:10:26,820 --> 00:10:30,420
But the unsub does,and you've already thought of this.

176
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:32,930
I had considered it.

177
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:40,320
Hope you find it useful.

178
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:42,200
Dr. Landman?

179
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,490
How's mr. Middleton.

180
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:45,150
Patient will make a full recovery...

181
00:10:45,190 --> 00:10:47,460
as I told you he would.

182
00:10:51,530 --> 00:10:55,700
Radiology is set up to take photos and e-mail them out for consults.

183
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:58,370
Call hotch.We're gettin' the bullet to garcia.

184
00:10:58,370 --> 00:11:00,710
Fill him in on the shift change theory.

185
00:11:00,950 --> 00:11:02,550
Give me a second.

186
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,110
Yeah. Morgan.

187
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:06,540
Isn't this spooky?

188
00:11:06,570 --> 00:11:07,880
Isn't what spooky?

189
00:11:07,910 --> 00:11:09,740
That right now you were thinking about me,

190
00:11:09,780 --> 00:11:11,760
and out of the blue,your phone rings?

191
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:13,510
And it's me. Huh?

192
00:11:13,540 --> 00:11:15,590
How's that for a spiritual connection?

193
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:17,290
Um... do I know you?

194
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:19,240
Why do you hurt me?

195
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:22,750
Garcia,please tell me you've nailed down the geographic profile on our guy.

196
00:11:22,790 --> 00:11:24,980
Ok,I'll give you the good news first,which is not that good,

197
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:26,930
but it's better than the bad.

198
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:30,250
We think the shooter has intimate knowledge of law enforcement procedures.

199
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:31,020
Detective calvin,

200
00:11:31,090 --> 00:11:33,560
how far out of your jurisdiction was crime scene number 2?

201
00:11:33,590 --> 00:11:35,270
About a sixth of a mile. Why?

202
00:11:35,310 --> 00:11:36,330
If he knew how difficult it is

203
00:11:36,370 --> 00:11:39,130
for local police departments to interact with each other,

204
00:11:39,180 --> 00:11:43,140
he may have intentionally crossed jurisdiction lines.

205
00:11:45,050 --> 00:11:47,950
- Y'all are sayin' the shooter's a cop.
- We're saying it's a possibility.

206
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,770
He scouted and prepped each crime scene.

207
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:53,490
He chose and elevated position with excellent enfilade and perfect field of fire.

208
00:11:53,510 --> 00:11:55,220
- That's textbook military practice.
- True.

209
00:11:55,260 --> 00:11:57,270
Yeah,but maybe he was in the army.

210
00:11:57,310 --> 00:12:00,370
He was probably a marine,ranger or other specialized unit.

211
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:04,500
Garcia says the bullet was a .223 fired from the m-4 variant of the m-16.

212
00:12:04,540 --> 00:12:06,180
All the services use an m-4.

213
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:08,090
It's got a shorter barrel than the m-16.

214
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:11,240
It's less accurate,and it's a lot harder to fire,especially at these distances.

215
00:12:11,260 --> 00:12:13,680
This level of skill indicates specialized training.

216
00:12:13,680 --> 00:12:15,560
If he has specialized training,

217
00:12:15,580 --> 00:12:17,190
he knows exactly what he's doing.

218
00:12:17,210 --> 00:12:19,730
- He intended to wound them.
- The underkill is deliberate.

219
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:20,970
Everything he does is deliberate,

220
00:12:21,010 --> 00:12:23,270
but it's as if he needs to show us how smart he is.

221
00:12:23,300 --> 00:12:25,940
Since the crime scenes aren't centered around one single location,

222
00:12:25,970 --> 00:12:28,910
garcia can't get a geographic profile without additional data.

223
00:12:28,940 --> 00:12:31,570
- What kind of data?
- More crime scenes.

224
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,410
She's gonna get 'em.

225
00:12:33,470 --> 00:12:35,870
This guy's got something to prove.

226
00:12:41,290 --> 00:12:43,530
- How did it play out?
- He's been suspended

227
00:12:43,550 --> 00:12:46,050
but my guess is that the school board's gonna go after him,

228
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:49,140
and they're gonna try to expel him.

229
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:56,110
I don't feel very good.

230
00:12:56,540 --> 00:12:58,500
I'm gonna go to the ladies' room,ok?

231
00:12:58,540 --> 00:12:59,980
Ok.

232
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:05,580
Honey,you have something on your dress.

233
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:24,360
3 more victims with nonfatal wounds,

234
00:13:24,390 --> 00:13:27,280
and it's only been 48 hours since the last shooting.

235
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:32,450
The media attention and the fbi presence will only escalate his desire to shoot again.

236
00:13:32,510 --> 00:13:34,310
Meaning?

237
00:13:34,710 --> 00:13:36,260
This is gonna get much worse.

238
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:38,260
The we need to give the police a profile immediately.

239
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:40,470
- You ready?
- State troopers.

240
00:13:40,490 --> 00:13:43,400
This is the second time he's crossed jurisdictions.

241
00:13:43,450 --> 00:13:46,550
Yeah,we're ready.They're not gonna like it.

242
00:13:47,270 --> 00:13:51,260
This initial profile is not ready to be given to the media.

243
00:13:51,290 --> 00:13:56,130
Releasing this profile prematurely can get people killed.

244
00:13:59,730 --> 00:14:02,080
We're looking for a 30 to 40-year-old male veteran,

245
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:04,090
driving a car large enough to shoot from,

246
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:06,200
but not so large it was noticed.

247
00:14:06,230 --> 00:14:08,400
Like the beltway shooter,it's probably a sedan,

248
00:14:08,450 --> 00:14:12,850
customized to conceal the shooter,his weapon,and the sound of his shot.

249
00:14:14,970 --> 00:14:19,270
The unsub suffers from both narcissistic and paranoid personality disorders.

250
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:21,910
He works out obsessively and is never without a weapon.

251
00:14:21,940 --> 00:14:24,990
He's completely self-centered and cannot empathize with others.

252
00:14:25,040 --> 00:14:26,330
Incapable of admitting fault,

253
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:28,840
